Location map of Western Quebec name Western Quebec border

coordinates 49.17 -79.78 ←↕→ -71.45 45.31 map center image Canada Western Quebec location map.png

Module:Location map/data/Canada Quebec Western is a location map definition used to overlay markers and labels on an equirectangular projection map of Western Quebec. The markers are placed by latitude and longitude coordinates on the default map or a similar map image.

Usage

These definitions are used by the following templates when invoked with parameter "Canada Quebec Western":

{{Location map|Canada Quebec Western |...}}

{{Location map many|Canada Quebec Western |...}}

{{Location map+|Canada Quebec Western |...}}

{{Location map~|Canada Quebec Western |...}}

Map definition

name = Western Quebec

Name used in the default map caption

image = Canada Western Quebec location map.png

The default map image, without "Image:" or "File:"

top = 49.17

Latitude at top edge of map, in decimal degrees

bottom = 45.31

Latitude at bottom edge of map, in decimal degrees

left = -79.78

Longitude at left edge of map, in decimal degrees

right = -71.45

Longitude at right edge of map, in decimal degrees

Precision

Longitude: from West to East this map definition covers 8.33 degrees.

At an image width of 200 pixels, that is 0.0416 degrees per pixel.

At an image width of 1000 pixels, that is 0.0083 degrees per pixel.

Latitude: from North to South this map definition covers 3.86 degrees.

At an image height of 200 pixels, that is 0.0193 degrees per pixel.

At an image height of 1000 pixels, that is 0.0039 degrees per pixel.

See also

Location map templates

Template:Location map, to display one mark and label using latitude and longitude

Template:Location map many, to display up to nine marks and labels

Template:Location map+, to display an unlimited number of marks and labels
